# Organic Fractals

2D Organic Fractals discovered in Apophysis. An interpretation of nature, inspired by wabi-sabi, finding the balance between calculation and chaos, and the beauty within it.

I was interested in fractals and computer-generated art since 2009, when I first discovered Aphophysis, but I didn't pursue it further, because I fought with the preconceived notion that something generated by a computer couldn't be considered "real art".

Now with the rise of cryptocurrency and NFTs, artforms that weren't formally recognized by institutions such as street art, memes, AI generated art, processing, and fractals are gaining appreciation and recognition from the right audience.

In that spirit, I picked up Aphophysis again, and started creating a series of pieces that is my take on deriving the organic from the digital, the random chance from the calculations, and the appreciation of the transient and imperfect (wabi-sabi).

With each of these pieces, I'm including the .flame file that contains the parameters which allow you to re-render this exact piece so you can make your own transformations.

Certain pieces have movement, so to click through to see which.

####Lychi 2021
